Autonomic hyperreflexia during cystoscopy in patients with high spinal cord injuries. Cystoscopic procedures were performed on 102 patients with histories of traumatic spinal cord lesion 57 patients had sensorimotor levels above T7, and the remaining 45 patients had levels below T7. In 40 of the 57 patients (70 per cent) with levels above T7, signs and symptoms of autonomic hyperreflexia were seen during bladder distension and cystoscopy